  "texts": [
    "Similarly, c σ ∈ [0, 1] controls the ill-posedness of the problem: smaller values indicate faster decay of singular values and hence more severe ill-posedness.",
    "Figure 2:2Figure 2: Comparison of the spectral methods' performance depending on the alignment of h 0 with the singular functions of T. Blue: True h 0; Orange: 2SLS estimate.",
    "Figure 3:3Figure 3: Example image from the dSprites dataset.The dSprites dataset, as employed in the evaluation of IV models, consists of 64 × 64 noisy images of hearts, with varying x, y positions, orientations and sizes.",
    "The full setting is as follows; X ∈ R 64×64 is the raw image, Z ∈ R 3 consists of the x position, orientation and scale of the heart in the image, and the output is constructed as5 Y = h 0 (X) + 32 • (y position -32) + U, U ∼ N (0, 1), where h 0 (X) = (∥A • X∥ 2 -3000)/500, A ij = |32 -j|/32.",
    "It was observed by Sun et al. [36] that spectral methods significantly outperform alternatives in this setting."
  ]
